details:
Case 122 is a 64 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is a close contact of Case 117, and is linked to the cluster involving the private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong.

She reported onset of symptoms on 3 March and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 5 March. She was referred to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on the same day, and was immediately isolated. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 5 March afternoon.

Prior to hospital admission, she had visited Westgate (3 Gateway Drive) and Keat Hong Community Club (2 Choa Chu Kang Loop). She stays at Petir Road.
